howToCreatePlugin: How to create a CS plugin?
inputPluginName: Give your plugin a resounding name
inputRepoName: Used to generate Tencent Cloud Dev Platform projects, only supports numbers, letters, underscores (_), and underscores (-)
inputPluginDesc: Briefly describe the role of this plugin, up to 255 characters
inputReleaseNote: Please enter the feature record added or modified in this release.
publishTip: Make sure the remote repo of the current plugin exists before publishing, and the latest code has been pushed to the repo.
prePublishTip: Pre-Publish will only install the plugin in all of your own workspaces, and the official Publish will be submitted to the backend and will be entered into the plugin market after being approved.
versionTip: The new version must be higher than the old version
status0: Your plugin has not been published yet and is not visible to the outside world. You can switch to the official release to publish the plugin.
status1: Your plugin v{{version}} version is under review, usually 3-5 business days, during which you can't publish it, please be patient.
status2: Your plugin failed to be approved due to {{reason}}
status3: Your plugin v{{version}} version is approved and is being built...
status4: Your plugin has an error while building. Please view the error log at Version History tab below.
status5: Your plugin v{{version}} version was published successfully!
hasPrePublish: The plugin is pre-published and you can preview it in all your workspaces.
cannotPublishForAuditing: The last release is under review and is temporarily unavailable
cannotPublishForBuilding: The last release is been building and is temporarily unavailable
gameTip: The Cloud Studio plugin development contest is in progress. If you are interested in the editor plugin, you can click the button below to participate in the contest. If your plugin is popular with developers, you will also receive a grand prize.
prePublishBuilding: Your Pre-Publish is been building, please wait...
